**Summary of fixes:**

1. **`job_queue.py:21-23`** — Moved `job["status"] = "processing"` before the `await`. Status now atomically transitions to `processing` before yielding control, preventing concurrent workers from seeing the same job as `pending`.

2. **`worker.py:20`** — Added `queue.fail(job["id"], str(e))` in the exception handler. Now failed jobs properly transition to either `pending` (for retry) or `failed` (when retries exhausted).
